
Macro: LOCALLY

Syntax:   (LOCALLY declarations &body body)

Returns:

 The value of the last form in body.

Processing:

 This provdes a way of associating declarations with one or more
 forms without having to provide a binding construct like LET or
 LAMBDA.

Errors signaled:

 None.

Notes:

Examples:

 (SET 'A 'FOO)                                 ==> FOO
 (LOCALLY (DECLARE (SPECIAL A)) A)             ==> FOO

